<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idf6543a95-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s2106"><num value="2106">§ 2106.</num><heading> Liability in rem</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">When a vessel is made liable in rem under this subtitle, the vessel may be libeled and proceeded against in the district court of the United States for any district in which the vessel is found.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idf6543a96-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5">(<ref href="/us/pl/98/89">Pub. L. 98–89</ref>, <date date="1983-08-26">Aug. 26, 1983</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/97/506">97 Stat. 506</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/109/304/s15/4">Pub. L. 109–304, § 15(4)</ref>, <date date="2006-10-06">Oct. 6, 2006</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/120/1702">120 Stat. 1702</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
